     1	"""Commander-backed provider.
     2	
     3	Wraps Commander via subprocess for simple commands and direct in-process
     4	command classes for PAM commands that need the logged-in session. This provider
     5	is the production path today: Commander already implements record I/O, rotation
     6	wiring, KSM binding, gateway registration, and share graph, so we reuse it
     7	instead of re-implementing.
     8	
     9	Commands used:
    10	    keeper pam project import --file <manifest>.pam_import.json
    11	    keeper pam project extend --file <manifest>.pam_import.json
    12	    keeper ls <folder_uid> --format json
    13	    keeper get <uid> --format json
    14	    keeper rm <uid>
    15	    keeper-vault.v1 (slice 1): in-process ``RecordAddCommand`` (record-add) for
    16	    ``login`` creates; ``RecordEditCommand`` merges manifest drift into existing
    17	    v3 JSON then :meth:`_write_marker` refreshes ownership metadata; same ``ls`` /
    18	    ``get`` discover path filtered to ``login`` rows.
    19	    keeper-vault-sharing.v1 (provider helpers): ``mkdir -uf``, ``mkdir -sf``,
    20	    ``mv --user-folder/--shared-folder``, ``rmdir -f``, ``share-record``,
    21	    ``share-folder``, and ``get <shared_folder_uid> --format json``.
    22	
    23	The provider:
    24	    1. Lists the target folder (if configured) and fetches each record.
    25	    2. Decodes ownership markers from the custom field.
